<p>
  <span class="nym">Madog</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym">A derivative of <span class="lang">Old Breton</span>, <span class="lang">Middle Welsh</span> <i>mat</i> 'good, fortunate'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a 6th-7th C Irish saint, a legendary 12th C Welsh explorer who purportedly reached America, two 12th C princes of Powys, and two 13th C princes of Powys.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>In early Arthurian literature, <i>Madoc</i> is the name of a son of Uther and brother of Arthur.</p>
</div>
  


